article.headline: TCU 62, Colorado 46
article.story: BOULDER, Colo. -- Zvonko Buljan and Keion Mitchem scored 15 points apiece to lead TCU to a 62-46 win over Colorado for the Horned Frogs' fourth consecutive victory Wednesday night. Kevin Langford added 10 points for TCU (5-3), which outscored the Buffaloes 12-0 over the first 6:07 of the game and went into the break with a 24-14 lead. Buljan put a stamp on the win -- only TCU's third in its past 16 meetings with Big 12 Conference schools -- on his breakaway dunk with eight minutes remaining to give TCU a 46-30 lead. Cory Higgins led Colorado (3-3) with 16 points, but the Buffs appeared out of sorts offensively without point guard Nate Tomlinson, who did not play. There was no immediate explanation for why he was out. Colorado's next highest scorer, Austin Dufault, finished with eight points. The Buffs, who shot at least 50 percent from the field in four of five previous games, hit only 28 percent of their first-half shots and finished with 40.5 percent for the game. TCU shot 46 percent from the field.
